description: Creates a VPC link, under the caller's account in a selected region, in an asynchronous operation that typically takes 2-4 minutes to complete and become operational. The caller must have permissions to create and update VPC Endpoint services.

parameters.name: name
parameters.description: The name used to label and identify the VPC link.

parameters.name: targetArns
parameters.description: The ARN of the network load balancer of the VPC targeted by the VPC link. The network load balancer must be owned by the same Amazon Web Services account of the API owner. (string) ---

parameters.name: tags
parameters.description: The key-value map of strings. The valid character set is [a-zA-Z+-=._:/]. The tag key can be up to 128 characters and must not start with aws:. The tag value can be up to 256 characters. (string) --- (string) ---

nested_items.name: id
nested_items.description: The identifier of the VpcLink. It is used in an Integration to reference this VpcLink.

nested_items.name: name
nested_items.description: The name used to label and identify the VPC link.

nested_items.name: description
nested_items.description: The description of the VPC link.

nested_items.name: targetArns
nested_items.description: The ARN of the network load balancer of the VPC targeted by the VPC link. The network load balancer must be owned by the same Amazon Web Services account of the API owner.

nested_items.name: status
nested_items.description: The status of the VPC link. The valid values are AVAILABLE, PENDING, DELETING, or FAILED. Deploying an API will wait if the status is PENDING and will fail if the status is DELETING.

nested_items.name: statusMessage
nested_items.description: A description about the VPC link status.
